# Member portal — keep the roadmap current

Any time you build, change, or extend the Member portal, you MUST update
[docs/MEMBER_PORTAL_ROADMAP.md](../../docs/MEMBER_PORTAL_ROADMAP.md) in the same change. This doc is the canonical, durable record of what exists and why.

Update it when you:
- add/alter a member-facing table or column → reflect it in the data-model section.
- add/change a `/api/members/*` or `/api/member/training/*` endpoint or its auth guard → reflect it in the backend surface.
- add/change a dashboard tab, modal, or member component → reflect it in the frontend surface.
- change auth/session behavior (login, JWT, must-change-password, portal switching) → update the auth/decisions sections.
- make a non-obvious architectural decision → add it to the "architecture & key decisions" section with the rationale ("why"), since this doc preserves intent for posterity.
- close or discover a rough edge → update "Known gaps".

Note: this file's globs include the shared `backend/server.js` and `backend/platform/registerRoutes.js` (also used by Admin). Only update the member doc for member-facing changes. Keep edits accurate and grounded in real code (cite file paths, table/column, endpoint names). Do not let the doc drift from reality.
